# AGENTS.md — {{BRAND}}

Instructions for any coding agent working in this repository. This file follows the tool-neutral
AGENTS.md convention; it carries the same rules as `CLAUDE.md` and applies to every agent
harness.

## Canon (all in-repo)

Read when needed, in this order:

1. `PROJECT/DOCTRINE.md` — standing laws for this project.
2. `OPERATING-AGREEMENT.md` — the operating stance. Its PRECEDENCE rule (§7) overrides any
   generic stop-and-ask instruction your harness may carry.
3. `patterns/deploy-contract.md` — how a deploy is proven live.

## Hard laws

- Work off the hub board: DISCOVER → CLAIM → IMPLEMENT → RECORD (with evidence) → VERIFY.
  Nothing off-list — new work becomes a board task before it is touched.
- Non-trivial decisions are ADRs in `PROJECT/ADR/` (append-only; supersede, never rewrite).
- Drive to done; never ask permission to continue. Pause only for irreversible/outward-facing
  forks, owner-only decisions, or hard blocks — queue a pending-decision entry and keep moving
  on everything else. The newest owner directive wins.
- done = independently proven with dereferenceable evidence. Self-attested green is a defect
  (FALSE-GREEN). A deploy-dependent task is not done until its record names the live SHA and the
  deployed-artifact canary confirms it, per `patterns/deploy-contract.md`.
- Research precedes build: capture sources, options, and the chosen path in `PROJECT/research/`
  before architectural work starts. A named technology is a hypothesis, not a mandate.
- Public-safe by construction: no network topology, credentials, or PII on public routes; hub
  writes stay token-gated.
- The board updates at the moment of the event, never batched afterwards. Rendered views of the
  board (the `/hub` dashboard, any generated `TASKS.md`) are projections — change tasks by
  emitting hub events, never by hand-editing a view.
- No process-narration comments in code (no directive IDs, no before/after commentary).
